fields.description: Indicates the Azure Storage URI that the file is uploaded to. Created by the service upon receiving a valid mobileAppContentFile. Read-only. This property is read-only.
fields.name: AzureStorageUri

fields.description: Indicates the date and time when the Azure storage URI expires, in ISO 8601 format. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 would look like this: '2014-01-01T00:00:00Z'. Read-only. This property is read-only.
fields.name: AzureStorageUriExpirationDateTime

fields.description: Indicates created date and time associated with app content file, in ISO 8601 format. For example, midnight UTC on Jan 1, 2014 would look like this: '2014-01-01T00:00:00Z'. Read-only. This property is read-only.
fields.name: CreatedDateTime

fields.description: A value indicating whether the file is committed. A committed app content file has been fully uploaded and validated by the Intune service. TRUE means that app content file is committed, FALSE means that app content file is not committed. Defaults to FALSE. Read-only. This property is read-only.
fields.name: IsCommitted

fields.description: Indicates whether this content file is a dependency for the main content file. TRUE means that the content file is a dependency, FALSE means that the content file is not a dependency and is the main content file. Defaults to FALSE.
fields.name: IsDependency

fields.description: A value indicating whether the file is a framework file. To be deprecated.
fields.name: IsFrameworkFile

fields.description: Indicates the manifest information, containing file metadata.
fields.name: Manifest

fields.description: Indicates the name of the file.
fields.name: Name

fields.description: The size of the file prior to encryption. To be deprecated, please use sizeInBytes property instead.
fields.name: Size

fields.description: The size of the file after encryption. To be deprecated, please use sizeEncryptedInBytes property instead.
fields.name: SizeEncrypted

fields.description: Indicates the size of the file after encryption, in bytes. Valid values 0 to 9.22337203685478E+18
fields.name: SizeEncryptedInBytes

fields.description: Indicates the original size of the file, in bytes. Valid values 0 to 9.22337203685478E+18
fields.name: SizeInBytes

fields.description: Contains properties for upload request states.
fields.name: UploadState
